d and `theirsValue` is undefined, and `baseValue` is also undefined, nothing to do.\n\n    mergedContent = resultObj; // This is the tentative merged content\n\n    return { mergedContent, conflicts };\n  }\n\n  // Helper to get all document IDs across two branches\n  private getAllDocumentIds(branchStateA: BranchState, branchStateB: BranchState): Set<string> {\n    const allDocIds = new Set<string>();\n    branchStateA.documents.forEach((_, docId) => allDocIds.add(docId));\n    branchStateB.documents.forEach((_, docId) => allDocIds.add(docId));\n    return allDocIds;\n  }\n}\n\n// Helper function to deep clone an object\nfunction deepClone<T>(obj: T): T {\n  // Handle null or non-object types\n  if (obj === null || typeof obj !== 'object') {\n    return obj;\n  }\n  // Use JSON.parse(JSON.stringify) for simple JSON-serializable objects.\n  // For more complex objects (e.g., with Date, RegExp, etc.), a more robust deep clone might be needed.\n  // Given the constraint \"Documents are plain JSON objects\", this should suffice.\n  try {\n    return JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(obj));\n  } catch (e) {\n    console.error(\"Deep clone failed:\", e);\n    throw new Error(\"Failed to deep clone document content.\");\n  }\n}\n```\nI have updated the `src/index.ts` file to include the merging logic. This includes:\n\n1.  **`findCommonAncestorVersionId`**: A helper to determine the latest common version ID of a document between two branches.\n2.  **`getVersionContent`**: A helper to retrieve the content of a specific version of a document from a given branch state.\n3.  **`performThreeWayMerge`**: The core recursive function that merges two document versions against a common base, identifying conflicts. It handles object properties, primitives, and also checks for deletions.\n4.  **`merge` method**: This method orchestrates the merge process by iterating through all documents present in either branch, finding their common ancestor, calling `performThreeWayMerge`, collecting resu